im_154","score":1},{"id":"reczzYTmzPPDcP3qv","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Reign of David","slug":"event-159","score":23}],"links":[{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recMYdxLC2GjLRomD","label":"part of"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recEdhjnlbofKC5rc","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"rec66ZgSDIRu3dVtZ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recwPUzr2MyOjkyLd","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recVSSxnkwRcwBSAD","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recGZnbyXQu695xNR","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"rec6D4qakD8wceZv8","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recP6fsKEckt8QTDh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recjLXb7c8RjZDfMS","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recFwUNeLQfVZZmCd","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"recrIxQuDpJHk9OiN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1GIDeWkCJCMQog","target":"reczzYTmzPPDcP3qv","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec381B5Elu3jqVn7","ref":"2Sam.16.1","text":"And when David was a little past the top of the hill, behold, Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth met him, with a couple of asses saddled, and upon them two hundred loaves of bread, and an hundred bunches of raisins, and an hundred of summer fruits, and a bottle of wine.","year":-1023},{"id":"recLAeImnYQnMNEC9","ref":"2Sam.16.2","text":"And the king said unto Ziba, What meanest thou by these? And Ziba said, The asses be for the king’s household to ride on; and the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat; and the wine, that such as be faint in the wilderness may drink.","year":-1023},{"id":"recLVwW2G8kfhi0C6","ref":"2Sam.16.3","text":"And the king said, And where is thy master’s son? And Ziba said unto the king, Behold, he abideth at Jerusalem: for he said, To day shall the house of Israel restore me the kingdom of my father.","year":-1023},{"id":"rec92iLueAmaFxCv3","ref":"2Sam.16.4","text":"Then said the king to Ziba, Behold, thine are all that pertained unto Mephibosheth. And Ziba said, I humbly beseech thee that I may find grace in thy sight, my lord, O king.","year":-1023},{"id":"recsAgzW3035GGRqj","ref":"2Sam.16.5","text":"And when king David came to Bahurim, behold, thence came out a man of the family of the house of Saul, whose name was Shimei, the son of Gera: he came forth, and cursed still as he came.","year":-1023},{"id":"recvazISGYEmOnr1s","ref":"2Sam.16.6","text":"And he cast stones at David, and at all the servants of king David: and all the people and all the mighty men were on his right hand and on his left.","year":-1023},{"id":"recPIuQatH2cvaxiN","ref":"2Sam.16.7","text":"And thus said Shimei when he cursed, Come out, come out, thou bloody man, and thou man of Belial:","year":-1023},{"id":"recQjqVAAuoPZmSne","ref":"2Sam.16.8","text":"The LORD hath returned upon thee all the blood of the house of Saul, in whose stead thou hast reigned; and the LORD hath delivered the kingdom into the hand of Absalom thy son: and, behold, thou art taken in thy mischief, because thou art a bloody man.","year":-1023}]}
